An estimate for the level of DNA methylation in a set of replicate samples that is calculated as the ratio of average signal intensities for methylated alleles divided by the average signal intensities of methylated alleles (M) plus unmethylated alleles (U) plus an offset factor (a), such that beta (b) equals M/(M+U+a).
